sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K199057
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: CCAUC tRNA (10-bp Anticodon) with RFP Reporter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: From the BioBrick Parts Registry. The tRNA was constructed by oligo assembly, and mutated the RFP reporter, [http://partsregistry.org/wiki/index.php?title=Part:BBa_E1010 E1010], to add the 5-bp insertion by PCR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Suppressor tRNA expressed by the medium-weak promoter, pBad, upstream of RFP with a 5-bp insertion, CCAUC. The tRNA is designed to suppress the insertion, allowing the appropriate translation of functional RFP.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: See the following parts for more information: [http://partsregistry.org/wiki/index.php?title=Part:BBa_K199008 CCAUC tRNA], [http://partsregistry.org/wiki/index.php?title=Part:BBa_K199032 pBad-tRNA] and [http://partsregistry.org/wiki/index.php?title=Part:BBa_K199009 RFP with 5-bp addition]. We wanted to create this composite so that the tRNA and reporter would be replicated in the same plasmid, and to be more efficient than a double transformation.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Olivia Ho-Shing

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: LacI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The Plac insert was PCR'd from the MG1655 strain of E.coli K12.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Inverting regulatory region controlled by LacI (BBa_C0010, BBa_C0011, etc.)

The pLac regulatory region is a 243 base-pair sequence with standard BioBrick prefix and suffix sections on its ends. It contains two protein binding sites: CAP, which is generally present in E.coli and is assocciated with cell health and availability of glucose., and LacI, the Lac inhibitor BBa_C0010 which binds in an dimerized cooperative manner to inhibit the transcription of the protein that follows. In the presence of lactose or IPTG, an analog of lactose, LacI is unable to correctly bind and inhibit transcription. This allows BBa_R0010 to be used as a inverter or as a detector of lactose or IPTG.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: LacI binds to this regulator. This part is incompatible with species containing active LacI coding regions. Lactose and IPTG disable the operation of LacI and this regulator. This part is incompatible with environments containing lactose or lactose analogs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I13453
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: PBad promoter from I0500 without AraC.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: jkm

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K199008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: CCAUC Suppressor tRNA (10-bp Anticodon and Produces Serine)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: De novo synthesis from single-stranded oligos. Based on the paper by Anderson et al. 2002. [http://gcat.davidson.edu/GcatWiki/images/6/6f/AndersonSchultz2002ChemBiol.pdf]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This gene encodes for a tRNA suppressor that suppresses a 5-bp codon CCAUC, which would normally cause a frame shift mutation.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We used the 10-bp anticodon loop that is complementary to the 5-bp codon CCAUC.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Olivia Ho-Shing

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K199009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The template of the gene comes from BioBrick Part E1010. We designed a forward primer that included ATG, the 5-bp addition CCATC and the first 20 nucleotides on the 5' end of RFP after ATG. This made the edited 5' sequence for our RFP.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This RFP reporter gene has a 5-bp addition, CCAUC, after the start codon and before the rest of the gene. This is used in conjunction with the CCAUC tRNA (Parts K199007 and K199008). These CCAUC tRNAs suppress the frameshift caused by this 5-bp addition in the reporter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We positioned the start codon, ATG, before the 5-bp codon and continued with the rest of the RFP gene. This way, the RBS wouldn't translate the reporter gene without reading over the 5-base codon first. In order to ligate our edited 5' sequence to the unchanged downstream portion of the RFP gene, we utilized the restriction enzyme NcoI that cuts at a single site 419-bp into BBa_E1010.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Olivia Ho-Shing
